        "content": "Hi Micah. A quick question about EIP1559: does `signature_y_parity` = `0x00` means `R.y` is odd or `R.y` is even? It is confusing for me as it is typed `bool` in the EIP1559, so I would expect `0x00` means `false` a.k.a odd, but this seems to contradict the old `v` parameter meaning (`v = y % 2`).",
        "created_at": "2022-12-14T16:22:22.311000+00:00",
        "attachments": null
    },
    {
        "author": "sky.cactus",
        "category": "Execution R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "`y_parity` is *not* the same as `v`.",
        "created_at": "2022-12-14T16:23:16.485000+00:00",
        "attachments": null
    },
    {
        "author": "sky.cactus",
        "category": "Execution R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "\u003e `YParity` The parity (0 for even, 1 for odd) of the y-value of a secp256k1 signature.",
        "created_at": "2022-12-14T16:24:03.614000+00:00",
        "attachments": null
    },
    {
        "author": "sky.cactus",
        "category": "Execution R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "EIP-2930 has a better definition: \u003chttps://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2930#specification\u003e",
        "created_at": "2022-12-14T16:24:24.761000+00:00",
        "attachments": null
    },
    {
        "author": "sky.cactus",
        "category": "Execution R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Which is where it first appeared in the protocol.",
        "created_at": "2022-12-14T16:24:30.278000+00:00",
        "attachments": null
    },
    {
